doc.previous: A mission modified Cessna 172 Skyhawk with a crew of two set the world record for continuous manned flight without landing of 64 days 22 hours 19 minutes and five seconds in 1958 by refueling and transferring food and supplies from a convertible top Ford Thunderbird automobile The publicity flight for a Las Vegas area hotel ended when the aircraft s performance had degraded to the point where the Cessna had difficulty climbing away from the refueling car 39 40
